pokemon.name: chespin
pokemon.text_entry: Such a thick shell of wood covers its head and back that even a direct hit from a truck wouldn’t faze it.

pokemon.name: quilladin
pokemon.text_entry: They strengthen their lower bodies by running into one another. They are very kind and won’t start fights.

pokemon.name: chesnaught
pokemon.text_entry: When it takes a defensive posture with its fists guarding its face, it could withstand a bomb blast.

pokemon.name: fennekin
pokemon.text_entry: As it walks, it munches on a twig in place of a snack. It intimidates opponents by puffing hot air out of its ears.

pokemon.name: braixen
pokemon.text_entry: When the twig is plucked from its tail, friction sets the twig alight. The flame is used to send signals to its allies.

pokemon.name: delphox
pokemon.text_entry: Using psychic power, it generates a fiery vortex of 5,400 degrees Fahrenheit, incinerating foes swept into this whirl of flame.

pokemon.name: froakie
pokemon.text_entry: It protects its skin by covering its body in delicate bubbles. Beneath its happy-go-lucky air, it keeps a watchful eye on its surroundings.

pokemon.name: frogadier
pokemon.text_entry: Its swiftness is unparalleled. It can scale a tower of more than 2,000 feet in a minute’s time.

pokemon.name: greninja
pokemon.text_entry: It appears and vanishes with a ninja’s grace. It toys with its enemies using swift movements, while slicing them with throwing stars of sharpest water.

pokemon.name: bunnelby
pokemon.text_entry: It’s very sensitive to danger. The sound of Corviknight’s flapping will have Bunnelby digging a hole to hide underground in moments.

pokemon.name: diggersby
pokemon.text_entry: The fur on its belly retains heat exceptionally well. People used to make heavy winter clothing from fur shed by this Pokémon.

pokemon.name: fletchling
pokemon.text_entry: When this Pokémon gets excited, its body temperature increases sharply. If you touch a Fletchling with bare hands, you might get burned.

pokemon.name: fletchinder
pokemon.text_entry: Fletchinder are exceedingly territorial and aggressive. These Pokémon fight among themselves over feeding grounds.

pokemon.name: talonflame
pokemon.text_entry: Talonflame dives toward prey at speeds of up to 310 mph and assaults them with powerful kicks, giving the prey no chance to escape.

pokemon.name: scatterbug
pokemon.text_entry: The powder that covers its body regulates its temperature, so it can live in any region or climate.

pokemon.name: spewpa
pokemon.text_entry: The beaks of bird Pokémon can’t begin to scratch its stalwart body. To defend itself, it spews powder.

pokemon.name: vivillon
pokemon.text_entry: The patterns on this Pokémon’s wings depend on the climate and topography of its habitat. It scatters colorful scales.

pokemon.name: litleo
pokemon.text_entry: This hot-blooded Pokémon is filled with curiosity. When it gets angry or starts fighting, its short mane gets hot.

pokemon.name: pyroar
pokemon.text_entry: The temperature of its breath is over 10,000 degrees Fahrenheit, but Pyroar doesn’t use it on its prey. This Pokémon prefers to eat raw meat.

pokemon.name: flabebe
pokemon.text_entry: Flabébé wears a crown made from pollen it’s collected from its flower. The crown has hidden healing properties.

pokemon.name: floette
pokemon.text_entry: It gives its own power to flowers, pouring its heart into caring for them. Floette never forgives anyone who messes up a flower bed.

pokemon.name: florges
pokemon.text_entry: Its life can span several hundred years. It’s said to devote its entire life to protecting gardens.

pokemon.name: skiddo
pokemon.text_entry: If it has sunshine and water, it doesn’t need to eat, because it can generate energy from the leaves on its back.

pokemon.name: gogoat
pokemon.text_entry: They inhabit mountainous regions. The leader of the herd is decided by a battle of clashing horns.

pokemon.name: pancham
pokemon.text_entry: Wanting to make sure it’s taken seriously, Pancham’s always giving others a glare. But if it’s not focusing, it ends up smiling.

pokemon.name: pangoro
pokemon.text_entry: Using its leaf, Pangoro can predict the moves of its opponents. It strikes with punches that can turn a dump truck into scrap with just one hit.

pokemon.name: furfrou
pokemon.text_entry: Left alone, its fur will grow longer and longer, but it will only allow someone it trusts to cut it.

pokemon.name: espurr
pokemon.text_entry: There’s enough psychic power in Espurr to send a wrestler flying, but because this power can’t be controlled, Espurr finds it troublesome.

pokemon.name: meowstic-male
pokemon.text_entry: The defensive instinct of the males is strong. It’s when they’re protecting themselves or their partners that they unleash their full power.

pokemon.name: honedge
pokemon.text_entry: The blue eye on the sword’s handguard is the true body of Honedge. With its old cloth, it drains people’s lives away.

pokemon.name: doublade
pokemon.text_entry: The two swords employ a strategy of rapidly alternating between offense and defense to bring down their prey.

pokemon.name: aegislash-shield
pokemon.text_entry: Once upon a time, a king with an Aegislash reigned over the land. His Pokémon eventually drained him of life, and his kingdom fell with him.

pokemon.name: spritzee
pokemon.text_entry: The scent its body gives off enraptures those who smell it. Noble ladies had no shortage of love for Spritzee.

pokemon.name: aromatisse
pokemon.text_entry: The scents Aromatisse can produce range from sweet smells that bolster allies to foul smells that sap an opponent’s will to fight.

pokemon.name: swirlix
pokemon.text_entry: The sweet smell of cotton candy perfumes Swirlix’s fluffy fur. This Pokémon spits out sticky string to tangle up its enemies.

pokemon.name: slurpuff
pokemon.text_entry: Slurpuff’s fur contains a lot of air, making it soft to the touch and lighter than it looks.

pokemon.name: inkay
pokemon.text_entry: By exposing foes to the blinking of its luminescent spots, Inkay demoralizes them, and then it seizes the chance to flee.

pokemon.name: malamar
pokemon.text_entry: It’s said that Malamar’s hypnotic powers played a role in certain history-changing events.

pokemon.name: binacle
pokemon.text_entry: If the two don’t work well together, both their offense and defense fall apart. Without good teamwork, they won’t survive.

pokemon.name: barbaracle
pokemon.text_entry: Having an eye on each palm allows it to keep watch in all directions. In a pinch, its limbs start to act on their own to ensure the enemy’s defeat.

pokemon.name: skrelp
pokemon.text_entry: Skrelp looks like a piece of rotten seaweed, so it can blend in with seaweed drifting on the ocean and avoid being detected by enemies.

pokemon.name: dragalge
pokemon.text_entry: Dragalge generates dragon energy by sticking the plume on its head out above the ocean’s surface and bathing it in sunlight.

pokemon.name: clauncher
pokemon.text_entry: By detonating gas that accumulates in its right claw, this Pokémon launches water like a bullet. This is how Clauncher defeats its enemies.

pokemon.name: clawitzer
pokemon.text_entry: Clawitzer’s right arm is a cannon that launches projectiles made of seawater. Shots from a Clawitzer’s cannon arm can sink a tanker.

pokemon.name: helioptile
pokemon.text_entry: The sun powers this Pokémon’s electricity generation. Interruption of that process stresses Helioptile to the point of weakness.

pokemon.name: heliolisk
pokemon.text_entry: One Heliolisk basking in the sun with its frill outspread is all it would take to produce enough electricity to power a city.

pokemon.name: tyrunt
pokemon.text_entry: Tyrunt is spoiled and selfish. It may just be trying to frolic, but sometimes the ones it’s trying to frolic with are gravely injured.

pokemon.name: tyrantrum
pokemon.text_entry: Complete restoration is impossible, allowing room for theories that its entire body was once covered in a feather-like coat.

pokemon.name: amaura
pokemon.text_entry: Amaura was restored successfully, but it’s not expected to live long because of the heat of the current environment.

pokemon.name: aurorus
pokemon.text_entry: This usually quiet and kindly Pokémon has a surface temperature of around –240 degrees Fahrenheit.

pokemon.name: sylveon
pokemon.text_entry: There’s a Galarian fairy tale that describes a beautiful Sylveon vanquishing a dreadful dragon Pokémon.

pokemon.name: hawlucha
pokemon.text_entry: It always strikes a pose before going for its finishing move. Sometimes opponents take advantage of that time to counterattack.

pokemon.name: dedenne
pokemon.text_entry: Since Dedenne can’t generate much electricity on its own, it steals electricity from outlets or other electric Pokémon.

pokemon.name: carbink
pokemon.text_entry: To keep the jewels on their bodies free of tarnish, packs of Carbink use their soft manes to polish one another’s jewels.

pokemon.name: goomy
pokemon.text_entry: Their horns are powerful sensors. As soon as Goomy pick up any sign of enemies, they go into hiding. This is how they’ve survived.

pokemon.name: sliggoo
pokemon.text_entry: The lump on its back contains its tiny brain. It thinks only of food and escaping its enemies.

pokemon.name: goodra
pokemon.text_entry: Its form of offense is forcefully stretching out its horns. The strikes land 100 times harder than any blow from a heavyweight boxer.

pokemon.name: klefki
pokemon.text_entry: Klefki sucks in metal ions with the horn topping its head. It seems this Pokémon loves keys so much that its head needed to look like one, too.

pokemon.name: phantump
pokemon.text_entry: With a voice like a human child’s, it cries out to lure adults deep into the forest, getting them lost among the trees.

pokemon.name: trevenant
pokemon.text_entry: Small roots that extend from the tips of this Pokémon’s feet can tie into the trees of the forest and give Trevenant control over them.

pokemon.name: pumpkaboo-average
pokemon.text_entry: The light that streams out from the holes in the pumpkin can hypnotize and control the people and Pokémon that see it.

pokemon.name: gourgeist-average
pokemon.text_entry: In the darkness of a new-moon night, Gourgeist will come knocking. Whoever answers the door will be swept off to the afterlife.

pokemon.name: bergmite
pokemon.text_entry: This Pokémon lives in areas of frigid cold. It secures itself to the back of an Avalugg by freezing its feet in place.

pokemon.name: avalugg
pokemon.text_entry: As Avalugg moves about during the day, the cracks in its body deepen. The Pokémon’s body returns to a pristine state overnight.

pokemon.name: noibat
pokemon.text_entry: No wavelength of sound is beyond Noibat’s ability to produce. The ultrasonic waves it generates can overcome much larger Pokémon.

pokemon.name: noivern
pokemon.text_entry: Flying through the darkness, it weakens enemies with ultrasonic waves that could crush stone. Its fangs finish the fight.

pokemon.name: xerneas
pokemon.text_entry: When the horns on its head shine in seven colors, it is said to be sharing everlasting life.

pokemon.name: yveltal
pokemon.text_entry: When its life comes to an end, it absorbs the life energy of every living thing and turns into a cocoon once more.

pokemon.name: zygarde
pokemon.text_entry: Some say it can change to an even more powerful form when battling those who threaten the ecosystem.

pokemon.name: diancie
pokemon.text_entry: It can instantly create many diamonds by compressing the carbon in the air between its hands.

pokemon.name: hoopa
pokemon.text_entry: It is said to be able to seize anything it desires with its six rings and six huge arms. With its power sealed, it is transformed into a much smaller form.

pokemon.name: volcanion
pokemon.text_entry: It expels its internal steam from the arms on its back. It has enough power to blow away a mountain.
